  "text": "Quarter-final · 12 July 2026 · Kansas City. Final score: Argentina 3–1 Switzerland. Argentina outlasted Switzerland in extra time to set up a blockbuster semi-final with England.\n\nThe champions were made to work deep into extra time by a Swiss side riding the high of their shootout heroics.\n\nThe goals, in sequence: 10′ Alexis Mac Allister — 1–0; 68′ Dan Ndoye — 1–1; 114′ Julián Álvarez — 2–1; 121′ Lautaro Martínez — 3–1. That is 4 goals in all, Argentina accounting for 3 and Switzerland 1.\n\nAlexis Mac Allister headed in a Messi corner early, twice left unmarked and punishing it the second time. Dan Ndoye levelled with a tight-angle finish after a neat one-two, and Switzerland dug in for extra time. Then Julián Álvarez unleashed a wonderful strike from distance in the 112th minute, and Lautaro Martínez added late gloss to seal it. Argentina keep finding another gear when the tie demands it — the mark of a team that knows how to win these.\n\nMomentum, as ever in the knockouts, proved a fragile and fleeting thing.\n\nThe expected-goals picture tightened around every set piece and transition.\n\nFor the record, Argentina advanced. Goal, team and minute for every event above are Merkle-proven on Solana devnet via TxLINE; the scorer names are attributed from public match reports and aligned to the verified goals by team and order. Nothing here rests on the commentator's word alone.",
